%% Diagram: Multiplexed Streams over a Single Connection
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant Server

    Note over Client,Server: One TCP+TLS connection, three independent streams

    Client->>Server: HEADERS stream 1 — GET /critical.css
    Client->>Server: HEADERS stream 3 — GET /app.js
    Client->>Server: HEADERS stream 5 — GET /hero.jpg

    Server->>Client: HEADERS stream 1 — 200 OK
    Server->>Client: DATA stream 1 — CSS bytes
    Server->>Client: HEADERS stream 5 — 200 OK
    Server->>Client: DATA stream 5 — image chunk 1
    Server->>Client: HEADERS stream 3 — 200 OK
    Server->>Client: DATA stream 3 — JS bytes (DATA END_STREAM)
    Server->>Client: DATA stream 5 — image chunk 2 (DATA END_STREAM)

    Note over Client,Server: Server interleaves DATA frames without app-layer HOL blocking
